item.title: French Open WTA Leaders
item.description: We are just hours away from the women’s final at the 2017 French Open. After 126 matches, 25 year-old Simona Halep and 20 year-old Jelena Ostapenko are the last women’s players remaining. And, whatever the outcome on Saturday in Paris, the women’s tour will see a new French Open champion and new Grand Slam title-holder crowned. Embed from Getty Images A number of factors make the pairing in the Roland Garros women’s final surprising.
